			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Nuh Uh. its been tried, it dont work. <br> Trust me, I sent about 4 letters and emails to Gordon, when he asked that IF someone would give him an idea of what would be an enforced rp server he would do it. He's a liar, we have to admit it.  Were in 'his world now'. <br> They set the moto so they can use it as backup if anyone ever complained, no one said we have a right afterall, we're in their world.  <br>  <br> They have their servers for the pk's, hell they made a few to fix the quakers taste. (no offence to those that roleplay on the pk servers) and they have lots for those that don't like to fight people, those are the blue servers that all the powerlevelers go to. RP'ers, they can be shoved in between the two, we can live in both. Consider us a bacteria, were huge, but tiny and scattered everywhere, not focused together. We can adapt to almost any enviroment, but we cannot overcome our host. <br>  <br> Theres my analogy, if you can change my mind, good for you. Gordon really doesnt care, despite his friendly words on the boards. Send him an email, if you get a reply I will be shocked. <br>  <br>  <br> **Still waiting for the replies to his 4 emails he sent 6 months ago** <br>  <br> The besy you can do is keep coming together, go join the egroup, we need to see numbers there,  <br>  <br>  <a class=BoardRowBLink target="_blank" href="http://www.egroups.com/group/morellthuleRP">http://www.egroups.com/group/morellthuleRP</a>   <br>  <br> Sign up, what do you have to lose? Joining guilds like Two Chalices are excellent too. It is not a real group, but just a name to say *HEY IM A ROLEPLAYER* From that you can still join other rp groups for reasons to be assisted by friends, but Two Chalices seems nice just to feel like you've got other roleplayers to talk to now and then with the /g you can converse about upcoming plots and stuff, thats what im trying to put together with the egroup listed above. Okay, This is probably getting boring to read now so I'll take it to an end. <br>  <br> Farewell... And good luck. (You'll need it) <br> 		

